.TH GEN-HTML "1" "December 2025" "gen-html 202208080003-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gen-html \- HTML file and website generator with templates
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gen-html
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR] [\fI\,ARGUMENTS\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gen-html
is an HTML file generator that creates HTML documents and complete website structures using customizable templates. It supports variable substitution, redirect page generation, and template management from local files or remote git repositories.
.PP
The script provides a streamlined workflow for creating consistent HTML files with automatic population of common elements like author information, timestamps, titles, and body content. Templates can be customized and stored locally for repeated use.
.PP
gen-html is designed for web developers who need to quickly scaffold HTML files or create simple websites without complex build tools.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B site
Set up a new complete website structure in the current directory. Copies all template files and applies variable substitutions for domain, author, and timestamps.
.TP
.B custom [url] [filename]
Use a custom template file from local path or remote URL. Downloads if URL provided, or uses local file if exists.
.TP
.B download
Download template files from the configured git repository to the custom templates directory.
.TP
.B list
List all available template files from both default and custom template directories.
.TP
.B redirect [url] [filename]
Create an HTML redirect page. If only URL provided, outputs to stdout. If filename provided, saves to file.
