.SH REDIRECT PAGES
The redirect command creates simple HTML redirect pages:
.PP
.B Generated redirect structure:
.RS
.EX
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="refresh" content="1; url='TARGET_URL'" />
    <title>Resource moved</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>Page has moved <a href="TARGET_URL">TARGET_URL</a></p>
  </body>
</html>
.EE
.RE
.PP
The redirect occurs after 1 second with a fallback link for browsers that don't support meta refresh.
.SH SITE COMMAND WORKFLOW
The site command creates a complete website structure:
.PP
.RS
.IP 1. 3
Copies all files from default template directory
.IP 2. 3
Applies variable substitutions to all HTML files
.IP 3. 3
Sets proper author, title, domain, and timestamp
.IP 4. 3
Creates index.html as the main entry point
.RE
.PP
.B Required directory structure:
.RS
The target directory should be empty or not contain existing HTML files to prevent conflicts.
.RE
.SH TEMPLATE MANAGEMENT
.SS Default Templates
Default templates are stored in ~/.config/myscripts/gen-html/files/ and are copied from:
.RS
.IP 1. 3
Configured git repository (GEN_HTML_REPO)
.IP 2. 3
System templates ($CASJAYSDEVDIR/templates/html/)
.RE
.SS Custom Templates
Custom templates in ~/.config/myscripts/gen-html/custom/ take precedence over default templates. Use the download command or manually copy files to this directory.
.SS Template Priorities
When generating files, templates are searched in order:
.RS
.IP 1. 3
Custom directory (~/.config/myscripts/gen-html/custom/)
.IP 2. 3
Default directory (~/.config/myscripts/gen-html/files/)
.IP 3. 3
System templates ($CASJAYSDEVDIR/templates/)
.RE
